&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Airtable is the no-code app platform that empowers people closest to the work to accelerate their most critical business processes. More than 500,000 organizations, including 80% of the Fortune 100, rely on Airtable to transform how work gets done.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Join DeepSkyâ€™s R&amp;amp;D team as a Product Designer and define the future of AI-powered superagents. Youâ€™ll drive the product design vision for our core agent interface, shaping how users interact with advanced AI to solve complex problems. This is a unique opportunity to lead design for a 0-1 product, influence go-to-market and growth strategy, and create delightful, accessible experiences that drive user adoption and retention. If you thrive at the intersection of technical systems, cognitive design, and product innovation, youâ€™ll find this role both challenging and rewarding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and champion a comprehensive product design vision and strategy for DeepSkyâ€™s AI superagent capabilities and user experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and address core user friction in onboarding, task delegation, and guided user journeys&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead end-to-end design for key product features, including Playbooks, Research Mode, dynamic user interactions, coding and browser agents, and complex reasoning delegation systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evolve and scale the DeepSky design system and information architecture to support new features and seamless human-agent interaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create high-fidelity prototypes and conduct user testing to validate design decisions and mitigate usability risks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate user education and accessibility into the product experience to drive adoption and trust&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with product, engineering, and GTM teams to deliver a cohesive product experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Must have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced product designer with a track record of 0-1 product design, especially in technical or cognitive systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong strategic problem framing and product sense, with demonstrated AI fluency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional design craft and attention to detail across consumer and data-oriented product systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid background: experience in agency, consumer/B2B hybrid, or non-software product systems (architecture, IPD, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent writing and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passionate about building delightful, accessible, and trustworthy user experiences that drive retention and conversion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Great to have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Startup experience, ideally as a founder or early team member&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tinkerer with a portfolio of side projects or self-initiated explorations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical background or experience in cognitive science, psychology, or related fields&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
